1
00:00:02,290 --> 00:00:07,590
I decided to try writing
a script for the first time in a while.

2
00:00:10,206 --> 00:00:12,837
I figured I'd write about Chika.

3
00:00:58,980 --> 00:01:01,947
Alright!

4
00:01:04,645 --> 00:01:06,239
Ta-da!

5
00:01:06,496 --> 00:01:08,292
Yay!

6
00:01:08,463 --> 00:01:09,982
Thank you!

7
00:01:12,690 --> 00:01:14,250
Here we go!

8
00:01:21,509 --> 00:01:24,963
- Shall we have some action tonight?
- I'm so glad to be alive!

9
00:01:51,501 --> 00:01:54,435
I Still Want to Do It with My Wife

10
00:01:55,193 --> 00:01:59,981
Final Episode: Doing It

11
00:02:13,739 --> 00:02:15,286
I'm off!

12
00:02:15,712 --> 00:02:17,050
Have a good day.

13
00:02:20,226 --> 00:02:21,739
Taro, I'm heading out.

14
00:02:21,779 --> 00:02:23,239
Bye, Mom!

15
00:02:44,809 --> 00:02:46,059
Whale!

16
00:02:46,066 --> 00:02:47,297
Jaws!

17
00:02:47,473 --> 00:02:48,678
Family!

18
00:02:49,118 --> 00:02:50,512
Um, crow!

19
00:02:50,740 --> 00:02:52,105
Horse!

20
00:02:52,400 --> 00:02:53,600
Tiger!

21
00:02:53,640 --> 00:02:55,066
Tapir!

22
00:03:05,813 --> 00:03:08,710
- Hi Gota!
- Oh, Midori!

23
00:03:08,750 --> 00:03:11,283
- Look at you, doing important stuff.
- Not really.

24
00:03:11,323 --> 00:03:16,593
Hey Mina, Taro's at Sunflower right now,
but it's almost over, so he'll be here soon.

25
00:03:17,139 --> 00:03:18,932
It's been a while, huh?

26
00:03:19,865 --> 00:03:23,606
- Wait, did you lose weight?
- Did I? I'm not sure.

27
00:03:23,646 --> 00:03:25,800
You look kinda sharp somehow.

28
00:03:25,910 --> 00:03:27,890
Like, cooler maybe.

29
00:03:27,930 --> 00:03:29,294
- Huh? Really?
- Totally.

30
00:03:29,334 --> 00:03:30,967
Mina, is that true?

31
00:03:31,291 --> 00:03:32,399
I dunno.

32
00:03:32,439 --> 00:03:34,084
You don't know, huh.

33
00:03:34,390 --> 00:03:35,913
- Dad.
- Oh, hello.

34
00:03:35,953 --> 00:03:37,200
I'm so tired.

35
00:03:38,207 --> 00:03:40,166
Come, Taro, let's go play!

36
00:03:40,206 --> 00:03:42,360
- Yeah, go on!
- Go have fun.

37
00:03:47,840 --> 00:03:51,384
Wait, did you get any results yet?

38
00:03:51,424 --> 00:03:53,234
Nah, not yet.

39
00:03:53,274 --> 00:03:56,426
Still not? Are you doing okay?

40
00:03:56,703 --> 00:03:59,935
Not really, no.

41
00:04:00,004 --> 00:04:02,150
I see.

42
00:04:02,615 --> 00:04:04,175
- Hang in there.
- Yeah.

43
00:04:04,560 --> 00:04:07,474
How about you?
Having fun with your boyfriend?

44
00:04:07,675 --> 00:04:10,010
- Oh, we broke up.
- Wait, seriously?

45
00:04:10,050 --> 00:04:14,250
He started calling Mina "hey you,"
so I kicked his ass out.

46
00:04:14,349 --> 00:04:17,750
- You kicked him out?
- Obviously.

47
00:04:18,014 --> 00:04:21,422
Besides, I already got a new boyfriend.

48
00:04:21,462 --> 00:04:23,242
- Already?
- Yep.

49
00:04:23,747 --> 00:04:25,066
Oh, there he is. It's him.

50
00:04:25,106 --> 00:04:27,272
Water gun attack!

51
00:04:28,896 --> 00:04:30,470
Huh?

52
00:04:30,510 --> 00:04:31,970
Is that guy okay?

53
00:04:32,010 --> 00:04:34,509
He's fine. He's actually a college professor.

54
00:04:35,531 --> 00:04:39,370
When you're as cute as I am,
you get matches right away.

55
00:04:39,658 --> 00:04:46,185
So I figured I'd meet tons of guys
and pick the best one of the bunch.

56
00:04:46,456 --> 00:04:47,853
Nice.

57
00:04:48,495 --> 00:04:53,450
Out of like a hundred guys,
there's gotta be one decent one, right?

58
00:04:53,490 --> 00:04:55,880
More like one out of a thousand.

59
00:04:55,920 --> 00:04:59,030
What the heck?!
Then it's enough if he's better than you.

60
00:04:59,070 --> 00:05:02,463
In that case, pretty much any guy qualifies.

61
00:05:02,611 --> 00:05:05,178
Wow, you're so honest today.
What's gotten into you?

62
00:05:05,218 --> 00:05:07,597
- What do you mean?
- Did something happen?

63
00:05:07,676 --> 00:05:09,280
- Wait.
- Huh?

64
00:05:09,290 --> 00:05:11,061
Did you fall for me a little?

65
00:05:13,590 --> 00:05:17,696
You guys haven't been
talking much lately, huh?

66
00:05:17,736 --> 00:05:19,563
- You think so?
- Yeah.

67
00:05:20,712 --> 00:05:23,066
It's nice that it's quieter now.

68
00:05:23,106 --> 00:05:26,952
But yeah, I wish you guys
would say something funny.

69
00:05:27,691 --> 00:05:29,852
You cheeky brat.

70
00:05:29,892 --> 00:05:33,070
- Papa can't say funny things anyway.
- Sure I can, right?

71
00:05:33,170 --> 00:05:34,603
Then say something.

72
00:05:34,643 --> 00:05:39,996
I gotta... poooop.

73
00:05:40,355 --> 00:05:41,569
See?

74
00:05:42,616 --> 00:05:45,260
- Then, make funny faces, Mama!
- Me again?

75
00:05:45,540 --> 00:05:48,470
Taro, you always ask me to make funny faces.

76
00:05:48,510 --> 00:05:50,150
Do it, do it, do it.

77
00:06:53,120 --> 00:06:56,720
- I love you.
- Well, I don't love you.

78
00:06:56,760 --> 00:06:59,667
The end.

79
00:07:34,369 --> 00:07:36,463
Hey, cut it out.

80
00:08:05,170 --> 00:08:07,490
Hey there. What's up?

81
00:08:07,689 --> 00:08:09,608
What's gotten into you?

82
00:08:09,648 --> 00:08:12,416
You could've just emailed me
the script, you know.

83
00:08:12,456 --> 00:08:17,757
Well, it didn't feel like that kind of thing.

84
00:08:18,057 --> 00:08:21,550
What? Is this serious stuff, then?

85
00:08:23,316 --> 00:08:24,750
That's right.

86
00:08:31,472 --> 00:08:33,845
I don't read stuff that isn't serious.

87
00:08:38,577 --> 00:08:42,317
I've always wanted to say
that line, just once.

88
00:08:42,550 --> 00:08:44,244
As a producer.

89
00:08:46,145 --> 00:08:49,169
Whenever you have time is fine.

90
00:08:49,209 --> 00:08:52,856
I'll read it now. You want me
to read it immediately, right?

91
00:08:54,643 --> 00:08:55,843
Yes.

92
00:08:58,450 --> 00:09:02,187
I wanna focus on reading it,
so go somewhere for a bit.

93
00:09:03,648 --> 00:09:04,998
Okay.

94
00:09:40,559 --> 00:09:44,181
Twelve years and seven months ago

95
00:09:44,372 --> 00:09:47,548
Okay, I finished reading it.

96
00:09:48,284 --> 00:09:50,148
How was it?

97
00:09:50,333 --> 00:09:52,134
I thought it was good.

98
00:09:52,277 --> 00:09:53,964
Really? You liked it?

99
00:09:54,004 --> 00:09:57,889
I totally loved it.
It's kinda like a Takeshi Kitano movie.

100
00:09:57,929 --> 00:10:02,740
Oh, that's good.
I'm so glad you picked up on that.

101
00:10:02,780 --> 00:10:04,173
That's my Chika.

102
00:10:04,213 --> 00:10:06,303
You really worked hard on it, right?

103
00:10:06,343 --> 00:10:09,509
Let's have some action
tomorrow morning as a reward.

104
00:10:09,658 --> 00:10:13,699
Yes! I feel like I’ve regained
the will to live.

105
00:10:13,906 --> 00:10:17,140
Hope this script does well.

106
00:10:17,186 --> 00:10:18,452
Yeah.

107
00:10:49,370 --> 00:10:50,676
I read it.

108
00:10:52,970 --> 00:10:55,217
Well, have a seat.

109
00:10:55,458 --> 00:10:56,679
Okay.

110
00:11:09,637 --> 00:11:12,091
Kaneto Shindo once said,

111
00:11:12,619 --> 00:11:17,186
"Anyone can write one masterpiece
in their lifetime."

112
00:11:18,229 --> 00:11:21,596
"All they have to do is
write about themselves."

113
00:11:23,310 --> 00:11:25,699
So you took that advice.

114
00:11:28,359 --> 00:11:30,214
Yeah.

115
00:11:32,290 --> 00:11:34,063
But this is

116
00:11:34,392 --> 00:11:35,753
not good at all.

117
00:11:37,530 --> 00:11:40,185
Your wife is written compellingly,

118
00:11:41,105 --> 00:11:45,697
but you, Yanagida, haven't bared yourself
at all as the main character.

119
00:11:47,290 --> 00:11:52,320
I mean, baring yourself isn't
everything, but still.

120
00:11:53,517 --> 00:11:56,004
If you strip your wife bare,

121
00:11:56,203 --> 00:12:00,157
but keep posing yourself,
it won't resonate with people.

122
00:12:02,897 --> 00:12:05,204
Well, I'm one to talk.

123
00:12:08,200 --> 00:12:11,051
Maybe I should bare myself, too.
Just kidding.

124
00:12:13,138 --> 00:12:17,065
Hey, don't look so down.
I'll send more work your way.

125
00:12:28,163 --> 00:12:32,618
Today we sang Doburock songs together
and talked about various things.

126
00:12:32,658 --> 00:12:36,827
He was able to express negative feelings too,
like why he doesn't like school.

127
00:12:36,867 --> 00:12:41,720
Being able to articulate his feelings
is real growth, I think.

128
00:12:44,671 --> 00:12:48,411
Even if I cause someone trouble

129
00:12:48,491 --> 00:12:51,740
It has nothing to do with me

130
00:12:51,780 --> 00:12:53,011
I'm home.

131
00:12:53,051 --> 00:12:55,636
I know nothing about that

132
00:12:55,676 --> 00:12:59,185
It just keeps turning and turning
and turning...

133
00:12:59,225 --> 00:13:04,083
- Taro, I'm home.
- Welcome back.

134
00:13:04,123 --> 00:13:11,216
The world revolves around me

135
00:13:11,256 --> 00:13:14,409
Egotistical, egotistical

136
00:13:14,962 --> 00:13:16,976
I am...

137
00:13:17,280 --> 00:13:20,745
The teacher at Sunflower says
the Ichimotsu Dance is her favorite.

138
00:13:20,785 --> 00:13:23,560
And she's a woman!
She's such a pervert. Right?

139
00:13:23,600 --> 00:13:26,264
Women can like
the Ichimotsu Dance too, you know.

140
00:13:26,304 --> 00:13:29,204
Mommy loves watching them sing
with those goofy grins, too.

141
00:13:29,244 --> 00:13:31,325
Ew, Mommy, you're weird too.

142
00:13:31,365 --> 00:13:35,055
Well, yeah, those faces are funny.

143
00:13:35,405 --> 00:13:38,731
By the way, I'm working hard at Sunflower,
so let me join the fan club!

144
00:13:38,771 --> 00:13:41,800
- I told you. When you're in sixth grade.
- Why? No way!

145
00:13:41,840 --> 00:13:45,641
- Here, eat up.
- No! I won't eat unless you let me join!

146
00:13:45,681 --> 00:13:48,273
If you eat, I'll think
about thinking about it.

147
00:13:48,320 --> 00:13:55,382
Seeing you in a yukata
makes me rock hard. Rock hard.

148
00:13:56,229 --> 00:13:59,422
Resting on your sash...

149
00:14:11,541 --> 00:14:14,316
Got a minute?

150
00:14:18,030 --> 00:14:19,398
Um...

151
00:14:22,117 --> 00:14:25,156
I finished writing a script.

152
00:14:28,244 --> 00:14:33,577
I had Yoyogi read it today.

153
00:14:38,321 --> 00:14:39,860
But it was no good.

154
00:15:13,546 --> 00:15:21,719
"After all, what did the crocodiles care
about a way to cross the river,"

155
00:15:22,116 --> 00:15:27,990
"and what a fine feast they were
carrying on their backs now!

156
00:15:28,249 --> 00:15:30,333
"As Elmer and the dragon..."

157
00:15:50,046 --> 00:15:51,806
What the hell is this title?

158
00:16:19,949 --> 00:16:21,580
You know,

159
00:16:22,550 --> 00:16:25,260
you used to be able to write
much better stuff.

160
00:16:27,873 --> 00:16:29,738
This isn't interesting at all.

161
00:16:30,638 --> 00:16:33,558
And, doesn't this make me
look like a horrible woman?

162
00:16:33,559 --> 00:16:36,146
Who said you could write about me anyway?

163
00:16:36,227 --> 00:16:38,020
This makes me sick.

164
00:16:45,570 --> 00:16:47,454
Hey, um...

165
00:16:50,522 --> 00:16:54,180
How about tonight?

166
00:16:55,470 --> 00:16:57,300
Shall we do it?

167
00:16:59,259 --> 00:17:02,029
What? What's wrong with your head?

168
00:17:03,160 --> 00:17:09,360
I figured... maybe we just have to do it.

169
00:17:10,324 --> 00:17:12,633
Huh? What the hell?

170
00:17:14,024 --> 00:17:18,732
Like maybe if we do it,
something will change.

171
00:17:18,772 --> 00:17:20,081
No, it won't.

172
00:17:20,121 --> 00:17:23,522
Yeah. Yeah, probably.

173
00:17:23,828 --> 00:17:27,169
I mean, nothing's gonna change at all, but...

174
00:17:29,529 --> 00:17:31,616
When marriages get like this...

175
00:17:36,437 --> 00:17:40,161
When things get desperate,
that's when the real fight begins.

176
00:17:41,378 --> 00:17:44,182
I think.

177
00:17:45,056 --> 00:17:50,081
So if we did it,

178
00:17:51,222 --> 00:17:54,423
it would feel like we're actually
in love with each other.

179
00:17:55,870 --> 00:18:00,028
I know this sounds really stupid,

180
00:18:00,071 --> 00:18:02,381
but I thought as long as we were doing it,

181
00:18:05,171 --> 00:18:10,724
you'd keep loving me forever.

182
00:18:11,728 --> 00:18:15,041
Part of me believed that.

183
00:18:15,081 --> 00:18:18,400
You really are a total idiot.

184
00:18:19,390 --> 00:18:20,632
Yeah.

185
00:18:21,395 --> 00:18:24,667
And you think being stupid is
kind of cute, don't you?

186
00:18:24,710 --> 00:18:31,795
No, not anymore.
Maybe a little in the past, but...

187
00:18:31,835 --> 00:18:36,169
No, you still do.
Because you're a genuine idiot.

188
00:18:39,899 --> 00:18:44,834
Since I'm a genuine idiot,
can I lay out our futon then?

189
00:18:44,874 --> 00:18:49,025
Seriously? How the hell did
this conversation lead to that?

190
00:18:49,065 --> 00:18:53,505
You really are stupid.
Oh, right, you were stupid. A genuine idiot.

191
00:18:59,218 --> 00:19:00,732
The real deal, seriously.

192
00:19:10,091 --> 00:19:12,999
I'll live my life however the hell
I want from now on.

193
00:19:14,112 --> 00:19:16,372
I won't care what happens to you anymore.

194
00:19:17,562 --> 00:19:18,762
Okay.

195
00:19:20,474 --> 00:19:22,219
Then let me come along.

196
00:19:22,259 --> 00:19:24,309
Don't you dare follow me.

197
00:19:27,996 --> 00:19:30,282
Then can I lay out the futon?

198
00:19:31,923 --> 00:19:37,213
I mean, if the answer's no,
I'll seriously back down.

199
00:19:37,253 --> 00:19:39,970
What do you mean, "seriously"?

200
00:19:46,590 --> 00:19:48,342
I'm not gonna do it.

201
00:19:50,390 --> 00:19:53,958
Right now,
I still don't want to do it with you.

202
00:19:54,471 --> 00:19:57,984
Even if we just let it happen,
nothing between us would change.

203
00:19:59,490 --> 00:20:03,600
We'd stay the same stupid married couple.

204
00:20:05,856 --> 00:20:10,183
You said in marriages, the real fight begins
when things get desperate, right?

205
00:20:11,615 --> 00:20:16,502
Then I'm making today our starting line.

206
00:20:21,293 --> 00:20:22,853
Anyway, I'm going to bed.

207
00:20:25,360 --> 00:20:26,775
Chika.

208
00:20:36,207 --> 00:20:37,740
I love you.

209
00:20:39,047 --> 00:20:40,780
Well, I don't love you.

210
00:20:45,680 --> 00:20:47,029
But...

211
00:20:52,058 --> 00:20:53,786
Whatever. Good night.

212
00:21:12,568 --> 00:21:17,601
I Still Want to Do It with My Wife
by Gota Yanagida
